{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":360,"text":"In half a century of trying to help prevent wars,"},{"time":4494,"text":"there's one question that never leaves me:"},{"time":8025,"text":"How do we deal with extreme violence"},{"time":11725,"text":"without using force in return?"},{"time":15226,"text":"When you're faced with brutality,"},{"time":17777,"text":"whether it's a child facing a bully on a playground"},{"time":20693,"text":"or domestic violence --"},{"time":22393,"text":"or, on the streets of Syria today,"},{"time":25309,"text":"facing tanks and shrapnel,"},{"time":27860,"text":"what's the most effective thing to do?"},{"time":31207,"text":"Fight back? Give in?"},{"time":33805,"text":"Use more force?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37176,"text":"This question: \"How do I deal with a bully"},{"time":41138,"text":"without becoming a thug in return?\""},{"time":44888,"text":"has been with me ever since I was a child."},{"time":47904,"text":"I remember I was about 13,"},{"time":50455,"text":"glued to a grainy black and white television in my parents' living room"},{"time":55441,"text":"as Soviet tanks rolled into Budapest,"},{"time":59706,"text":"and kids not much older than me"},{"time":62505,"text":"were throwing themselves at the tanks"},{"time":65006,"text":"and getting mown down."},{"time":67174,"text":"And I rushed upstairs and started packing my suitcase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70975,"text":"And my mother came up and said, \"What on Earth are you doing?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":73689,"text":"And I said, \"I'm going to Budapest.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":75971,"text":"And she said, \"What on Earth for?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":78605,"text":"And I said, \"Kids are getting killed there."},{"time":80654,"text":"There's something terrible happening.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":82506,"text":"And she said, \"Don't be so silly.\""},{"time":84523,"text":"And I started to cry."},{"time":87123,"text":"And she got it, she said,"},{"time":89338,"text":"\"Okay, I see it's serious."},{"time":91105,"text":"You're much too young to help."},{"time":93939,"text":"You need training. I'll help you."},{"time":96574,"text":"But just unpack your suitcase.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":98739,"text":"And so I got some training"},{"time":102305,"text":"and went and worked in Africa during most of my 20s."},{"time":106238,"text":"But I realized that what I really needed to know"},{"time":109939,"text":"I couldn't get from training courses."},{"time":112338,"text":"I wanted to understand"},{"time":114524,"text":"how violence, how oppression, works."},{"time":118974,"text":"And what I've discovered since is this:"},{"time":123922,"text":"Bullies use violence in three ways."},{"time":127988,"text":"They use political violence to intimidate,"},{"time":133291,"text":"physical violence to terrorize"},{"time":138705,"text":"and mental or emotional violence to undermine."},{"time":146229,"text":"And only very rarely in very few cases"},{"time":149456,"text":"does it work to use more violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152972,"text":"Nelson Mandela went to jail believing in violence,"},{"time":159181,"text":"and 27 years later"},{"time":161205,"text":"he and his colleagues"},{"time":163188,"text":"had slowly and carefully"},{"time":165173,"text":"honed the skills, the incredible skills, that they needed"},{"time":170139,"text":"to turn one of the most vicious governments the world has known"},{"time":174339,"text":"into a democracy."},{"time":176205,"text":"And they did it in a total devotion to non-violence."},{"time":180937,"text":"They realized that using force against force"},{"time":188104,"text":"doesn't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193300,"text":"So what does work?"},{"time":195493,"text":"Over time I've collected about a half-dozen methods"},{"time":198962,"text":"that do work -- of course there are many more --"},{"time":200795,"text":"that do work and that are effective."},{"time":203141,"text":"And the first is"},{"time":204508,"text":"that the change that has to take place"},{"time":207026,"text":"has to take place here, inside me."},{"time":211491,"text":"It's my response, my attitude, to oppression"},{"time":215591,"text":"that I've got control over,"},{"time":218442,"text":"and that I can do something about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220742,"text":"And what I need to develop is self-knowledge to do that."},{"time":224925,"text":"That means I need to know how I tick,"},{"time":227424,"text":"when I collapse,"},{"time":229675,"text":"where my formidable points are,"},{"time":234009,"text":"where my weaker points are."},{"time":236507,"text":"When do I give in?"},{"time":237975,"text":"What will I stand up for?"},{"time":243238,"text":"And meditation or self-inspection"},{"time":248377,"text":"is one of the ways -- again it's not the only one --"},{"time":250911,"text":"it's one of the ways"},{"time":252029,"text":"of gaining this kind of inner power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256146,"text":"And my heroine here -- like Satish's --"},{"time":258628,"text":"is Aung San Suu Kyi in Burma."},{"time":261661,"text":"She was leading a group of students"},{"time":265294,"text":"on a protest in the streets of Rangoon."},{"time":267694,"text":"They came around a corner faced with a row of machine guns."},{"time":271877,"text":"And she realized straight away"},{"time":273044,"text":"that the soldiers with their fingers shaking on the triggers"},{"time":276962,"text":"were more scared than the student protesters behind her."},{"time":282660,"text":"But she told the students to sit down."},{"time":285365,"text":"And she walked forward with such calm and such clarity"},{"time":292661,"text":"and such total lack of fear"},{"time":296111,"text":"that she could walk right up to the first gun,"},{"time":300211,"text":"put her hand on it and lower it."},{"time":308564,"text":"And no one got killed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312097,"text":"So that's what the mastery of fear can do --"},{"time":316039,"text":"not only faced with machine guns,"},{"time":318340,"text":"but if you meet a knife fight in the street."},{"time":322506,"text":"But we have to practice."},{"time":324871,"text":"So what about our fear?"},{"time":326772,"text":"I have a little mantra."},{"time":331726,"text":"My fear grows fat"},{"time":335167,"text":"on the energy I feed it."},{"time":337384,"text":"And if it grows very big"},{"time":339671,"text":"it probably happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342033,"text":"So we all know the three o'clock in the morning syndrome,"},{"time":346468,"text":"when something you've been worrying about wakes you up --"},{"time":349184,"text":"I see a lot of people --"},{"time":351574,"text":"and for an hour you toss and turn,"},{"time":355184,"text":"it gets worse and worse,"},{"time":356862,"text":"and by four o'clock you're pinned to the pillow"},{"time":359984,"text":"by a monster this big."},{"time":362187,"text":"The only thing to do"},{"time":364121,"text":"is to get up, make a cup of tea"},{"time":365955,"text":"and sit down with the fear like a child beside you."},{"time":371271,"text":"You're the adult."},{"time":373752,"text":"The fear is the child."},{"time":375639,"text":"And you talk to the fear"},{"time":377084,"text":"and you ask it what it wants, what it needs."},{"time":380270,"text":"How can this be made better?"},{"time":384887,"text":"How can the child feel stronger?"},{"time":386637,"text":"And you make a plan."},{"time":388086,"text":"And you say, \"Okay, now we're going back to sleep."},{"time":390091,"text":"Half-past seven, we're getting up and that's what we're going to do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":393858,"text":"I had one of these 3 a.m. episodes on Sunday --"},{"time":399606,"text":"paralyzed with fear at coming to talk to you."},{"time":403591,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":405589,"text":"So I did the thing."},{"time":407096,"text":"I got up, made the cup of tea, sat down with it, did it all"},{"time":411225,"text":"and I'm here -- still partly paralyzed, but I'm here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415381,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419780,"text":"So that's fear. What about anger?"},{"time":422296,"text":"Wherever there is injustice there's anger."},{"time":426698,"text":"But anger is like gasoline,"},{"time":429546,"text":"and if you spray it around and somebody lights a match,"},{"time":433000,"text":"you've got an inferno."},{"time":435000,"text":"But anger as an engine -- in an engine -- is powerful."},{"time":440117,"text":"If we can put our anger inside an engine,"},{"time":444283,"text":"it can drive us forward,"},{"time":446066,"text":"it can get us through the dreadful moments"},{"time":449054,"text":"and it can give us real inner power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453017,"text":"And I learned this in my work"},{"time":456135,"text":"with nuclear weapon policy-makers."},{"time":458399,"text":"Because at the beginning I was so outraged"},{"time":461118,"text":"at the dangers they were exposing us to"},{"time":464434,"text":"that I just wanted to argue and blame and make them wrong."},{"time":469568,"text":"Totally ineffective."},{"time":472101,"text":"In order to develop a dialogue for change"},{"time":475850,"text":"we have to deal with our anger."},{"time":477923,"text":"It's okay to be angry with the thing --"},{"time":482600,"text":"the nuclear weapons in this case --"},{"time":484700,"text":"but it is hopeless to be angry with the people."},{"time":488551,"text":"They are human beings just like us."},{"time":491166,"text":"And they're doing what they think is best."},{"time":493817,"text":"And that's the basis on which we have to talk with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497800,"text":"So that's the third one, anger."},{"time":500717,"text":"And it brings me to the crux"},{"time":502117,"text":"of what's going on, or what I perceive as going on,"},{"time":505351,"text":"in the world today,"},{"time":506416,"text":"which is that last century was top-down power."},{"time":510434,"text":"It was still governments telling people what to do."},{"time":514699,"text":"This century there's a shift."},{"time":516734,"text":"It's bottom-up or grassroots power."},{"time":520617,"text":"It's like mushrooms coming through concrete."},{"time":523833,"text":"It's people joining up with people, as Bundy just said, miles away"},{"time":530514,"text":"to bring about change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532787,"text":"And Peace Direct spotted quite early on"},{"time":537053,"text":"that local people in areas of very hot conflict"},{"time":540604,"text":"know what to do."},{"time":543040,"text":"They know best what to do."},{"time":545256,"text":"So Peace Direct gets behind them to do that."},{"time":548538,"text":"And the kind of thing they're doing"},{"time":550737,"text":"is demobilizing militias,"},{"time":553905,"text":"rebuilding economies,"},{"time":556508,"text":"resettling refugees,"},{"time":558858,"text":"even liberating child soldiers."},{"time":564359,"text":"And they have to risk their lives almost every day"},{"time":567225,"text":"to do this."},{"time":570444,"text":"And what they've realized"},{"time":574258,"text":"is that using violence in the situations they operate in"},{"time":579191,"text":"is not only less humane,"},{"time":583710,"text":"but it's less effective"},{"time":585845,"text":"than using methods that connect people with people, that rebuild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592376,"text":"And I think that the U.S. military"},{"time":596308,"text":"is finally beginning to get this."},{"time":603188,"text":"Up to now their counter-terrorism policy"},{"time":605897,"text":"has been to kill insurgents at almost any cost,"},{"time":610730,"text":"and if civilians get in the way,"},{"time":613933,"text":"that's written as \"collateral damage.\""},{"time":618199,"text":"And this is so infuriating and humiliating"},{"time":624932,"text":"for the population of Afghanistan,"},{"time":627282,"text":"that it makes the recruitment for al-Qaeda very easy,"},{"time":631630,"text":"when people are so disgusted by, for example,"},{"time":634800,"text":"the burning of the Koran."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637179,"text":"So the training of the troops has to change."},{"time":640180,"text":"And I think there are signs that it is beginning to change."},{"time":645288,"text":"The British military have always been much better at this."},{"time":648072,"text":"But there is one magnificent example for them to take their cue from,"},{"time":653754,"text":"and that's a brilliant U.S. lieutenant colonel"},{"time":656922,"text":"called Chris Hughes."},{"time":658587,"text":"And he was leading his men down the streets of Najaf --"},{"time":662804,"text":"in Iraq actually --"},{"time":664972,"text":"and suddenly people were pouring out of the houses on either side of the road,"},{"time":670005,"text":"screaming, yelling, furiously angry,"},{"time":674603,"text":"and surrounded these very young troops who were completely terrified,"},{"time":679071,"text":"didn't know what was going on, couldn't speak Arabic."},{"time":681571,"text":"And Chris Hughes strode into the middle of the throng"},{"time":685821,"text":"with his weapon above his head, pointing at the ground,"},{"time":689690,"text":"and he said, \"Kneel.\""},{"time":691388,"text":"And these huge soldiers"},{"time":694188,"text":"with their backpacks and their body armor,"},{"time":696821,"text":"wobbled to the ground."},{"time":701295,"text":"And complete silence fell."},{"time":707380,"text":"And after about two minutes,"},{"time":709938,"text":"everybody moved aside and went home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714214,"text":"Now that to me is wisdom in action."},{"time":719696,"text":"In the moment, that's what he did."},{"time":723862,"text":"And it's happening everywhere now."},{"time":729624,"text":"You don't believe me?"},{"time":731533,"text":"Have you asked yourselves"},{"time":735192,"text":"why and how so many dictatorships have collapsed"},{"time":739632,"text":"over the last 30 years?"},{"time":742983,"text":"Dictatorships in Czechoslovakia, East Germany,"},{"time":748050,"text":"Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania,"},{"time":752265,"text":"Mali, Madagascar,"},{"time":755151,"text":"Poland, the Philippines,"},{"time":758933,"text":"Serbia, Slovenia, I could go on,"},{"time":764016,"text":"and now Tunisia and Egypt."},{"time":768606,"text":"And this hasn't just happened."},{"time":772656,"text":"A lot of it is due to a book"},{"time":775807,"text":"written by an 80-year-old man in Boston, Gene Sharp."},{"time":780272,"text":"He wrote a book called \"From Dictatorship to Democracy\""},{"time":784289,"text":"with 81 methodologies for non-violent resistance."},{"time":789685,"text":"And it's been translated into 26 languages."},{"time":791772,"text":"It's flown around the world."},{"time":793856,"text":"And it's being used by young people and older people everywhere,"},{"time":801043,"text":"because it works and it's effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806465,"text":"So this is what gives me hope --"},{"time":811023,"text":"not just hope, this is what makes me feel very positive right now."},{"time":814776,"text":"Because finally human beings are getting it."},{"time":818792,"text":"We're getting practical, doable methodologies"},{"time":826410,"text":"to answer my question:"},{"time":827994,"text":"How do we deal with a bully without becoming a thug?"},{"time":834296,"text":"We're using the kind of skills that I've outlined:"},{"time":838706,"text":"inner power -- the development of inner power -- through self-knowledge,"},{"time":842424,"text":"recognizing and working with our fear,"},{"time":845990,"text":"using anger as a fuel,"},{"time":849508,"text":"cooperating with others,"},{"time":852073,"text":"banding together with others,"},{"time":854008,"text":"courage,"},{"time":856190,"text":"and most importantly, commitment to active non-violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863159,"text":"Now I don't just believe in non-violence."},{"time":867273,"text":"I don't have to believe in it."},{"time":870208,"text":"I see evidence everywhere of how it works."},{"time":873758,"text":"And I see that we, ordinary people,"},{"time":879808,"text":"can do what Aung San Suu Kyi and Ghandi and Mandela did."},{"time":886126,"text":"We can bring to an end"},{"time":888849,"text":"the bloodiest century that humanity has ever known."},{"time":893848,"text":"And we can organize to overcome oppression"},{"time":901789,"text":"by opening our hearts"},{"time":904407,"text":"as well as strengthening this incredible resolve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910257,"text":"And this open-heartedness is exactly what I've experienced"},{"time":914857,"text":"in the entire organization of this gathering since I got here yesterday."},{"time":919291,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921412,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}